         ChangeLog:
		 
		 1.03:  UTF-8 support.

         1.02:  Added LOG-check.

         1.01:  Added FLAC CUESHEET METABLOCK support
                (internal change, only affects mixed cds)


         ATTENTION! PLEASE READ OUR NOTES BELOW BEFORE USING
         TT LOSSLESS-Releaser 1.03:

         1. Flac.exe must be installed in path! For Example C:\Windows\
            You can test it, by opening a console and type "flac".
            If it's runinng, you're fine.

         2. Lossless-Releaser is made for EAC! Fill out the fields in
            EAC such as:

              - ARTIST          (can be done in EAC)
              - ALBUM           (can be done in EAC)
              - GENRE           (can be done in EAC)
              - YEAR            (can be done in EAC)
              - TRACK TITLE     (can be done in EAC)

              - COMPOSER        (can be added in foobar2000 as new tag)

            Those fields will be used to set proper FLAC tags.

         3. If it's a VA album, then put on the select box
            "Various Artists".

         4. If you use a LOG file do NOT change the log file
            before using TT LOSSLESS-Releaser 1.03.

         5. Do NOT run this program from your windows desktop it
            wont work. Install it in a proper directory on your
            C: drive.


         HOW TO USE IT:

         1. Put the ripped and tagged flacs in a directory i.e.
            c:\music optionally also put a LOG, CUE, JPG, PNG or ITC

            c:\music\va-top100hits.cue
            c:\music\va-top100hits.log
            c:\music\artwork.jpg
            c:\music\track1.flac
            c:\music\track2.flac
            c:\music\track3.flac
            ...

            note: naming does not matter!
                  (Only tracks have to be in order)

         2. Start TT LOSSLESS-Releaser 1.03, fill out the fields and
            press "Convert"

         3. If you have a 2-CD or 3-CD release put the files in:

            c:\music\cd1
            c:\music\cd2
            c:\music\cd3
            ...

            Each directory must have its own LOG, CUE and JPG file.


